  "texts": [
    "The purpose of the event detection algorithm development and workflow is to facilitate a consistent approach to the generation and analysis of event catalogues for cryoseismology and similar research.",
    "The varied nature of cryoseismicity raises the question of how an event should be defined for inclusion in the catalogue.",
    "Two definitions were tested with regard to how an event is detected by an array.",
    "In the first definition, we included a trigger condition that defined a detection when three or more seismometers were triggered within 60 s of the same arrival time.",
    "This biased the catalogue towards events with impulsive initial arrivals, resulting in events that we know to have a single source mechanism to be truncated prematurely or divided up into separate events."
  ],
